285 g Top Sirloin Steak
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
1 unit Mini Cucumber
56 g Carrot, julienned
7 g Cilantro
7 g Mint
1 unit Lime
28 g Peanuts, chopped
9 g Moo Shu Spice Blend
2 tbsp Tahini Sauce
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Fish Sauce
2.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
½ tsp Sugar*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high.
Meanwhile, cut cucumber into thin matchsticks.
Roughly chop cilantro.
Pick mint leaves from stems, then roughly chop.
Zest, then juice lime.
In a medium bowl, whisk together tahini sauce, soy sauce, half the Moo Shu Spice Blend, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lime juice, 1 tsp (2 tsp) lime zest, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 1/2 tbsp (3 tbsp) oil. (NOTE: This is your noodle sauce.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add peanuts to the dry pan. Toast for 4-5 min, stirring often, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn.)
Remove from heat.
Transfer to a plate.

Pat steaks dry with paper towels. Season with salt, pepper and remaining Moo Shu Spice Blend.
Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then steaks. Cook for 1-2 min per side, until browned. (NOTE: Steaks will finish cooking in step 4.)
Remove from heat. To an unlined baking sheet, transfer steaks.

Roast steaks in the top of the oven for 4-7 min, or until cooked to desired doneness.**
When steaks are done, transfer to a plate and set aside to rest for 2-3 min.

Meanwhile, to the boiling water, add noodles. Cook for 1-3 min, stirring occasionally, until tender but still firm to the bite.
Strain and rinse noodles with cold water.
Return noodles to the pot, add noodle sauce from step 1 and fish sauce, then toss to coat.

To the pot with dressed noodles, add carrots, cucumbers, half the cilantro, half the mint and half the peanuts, then toss to combine.
Thinly slice steak.
Divide noodles and steak between plates. Top steak with any resting steak juices.
Sprinkle remaining cilantro, remaining mint and remaining peanuts over top.